through the Montessori method.

00:08:56.710 --> 00:09:00.390 align:middle line:84%
Montessori paved the way ahead
for many alternative education

00:09:00.390 --> 00:09:01.260 align:middle line:90%
approaches.

00:09:01.260 --> 00:09:03.360 align:middle line:84%
And like a lot of
the big innovations

00:09:03.360 --> 00:09:06.000 align:middle line:84%
that address
problems at the roots

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:09.990 align:middle line:84%
of how society functions,
Montessori has also

00:09:09.990 --> 00:09:12.960 align:middle line:84%
had to open people's minds
to an alternative approach

00:09:12.960 --> 00:09:13.980 align:middle line:90%
to education.

00:09:13.980 --> 00:09:17.010 align:middle line:84%
Critique is inevitable when
we're changing the status quo.

00:09:17.010 --> 00:09:19.530 align:middle line:84%
And all alternative
education methods

00:09:19.530 --> 00:09:21.250 align:middle line:90%
have to deal with critique.

00:09:21.250 --> 00:09:24.660 align:middle line:84%
On that note, I do not
think it is a coincidence

00:09:24.660 --> 00:09:27.840 align:middle line:84%
that a relatively high
proportion of entrepreneurs

00:09:27.840 --> 00:09:30.640 align:middle line:84%
went through education
systems like Montessori.

00:09:30.640 --> 00:09:34.270 align:middle line:84%
Doing things differently and
questioning our environments

00:09:34.270 --> 00:09:36.340 align:middle line:90%
are key entrepreneurial skills.

00:09:36.340 --> 00:09:40.030 align:middle line:84%
And these methods usually
support a questioning

00:09:40.030 --> 00:09:41.820 align:middle line:90%
